				<<his>> attention to the <<= C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20 ? `news` : `football game`>>.
			<<else>>
				<<= C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20 ? `to <<his>> drinking` : `<<his>> attention to <<his>> paintings`>>.
			<</if>>
		<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "pool">>
			<<if $avery_pool is "swim">>
				You try to get Avery's attention, but <<he>> ignores you, and on <<his>> swimming. You get the feeling <<hes>> uninterested in further conversation.
			<<else>>
				<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
					glares and scowls.

					"Enough of this," <<he>> says before you can say anything. "I'm trying to spend my precious free time relaxing, and I won't have you wasting it by talking my bloody ear off. Leave me be." <<He>> makes a dismissive gesture,
				<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
					shoots you an irritated look.

					"Enough of this," <<he>> says before you can say anything. "I'm trying to spend my precious free time relaxing, and I won't have you wasting it with your inane chatter. Leave me be." <<He>> makes a dismissive gesture,
				<<else>>
					frowns <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `at you, brows furrowing,` : `a little`>> as you approach.

					"That's enough," <<he>> says before you can say anything. "I'm trying to spend my precious free time relaxing. I'm not interested in spending all of it <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `listening to you natter on` : `just talking`>>. And I'm sure you have more important things to do, anyway." <<He>>
				<</if>>
			then <<= $avery_pool is "sunbathe" ? `slides <<his>> sunglasses back into place` : `returns <<his>> attention to <<his>> phone`>>.
			<</if>>
		<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "garden">>
			<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
				glares and scowl.

				"Enough of this," <<he>> says before you can say anything. "Tending my garden takes focus<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("garden")>>, as you should know<</if>>, and I won't have you distracting me by talking my bloody ear off. Leave me be." <<He>> makes a dismissive gesture,
			<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
				shoots you an irritated look.

				"Enough of this," <<he>> says before you can say anything. "Tending my garden takes focus<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("garden")>>, as you should know<</if>>, and I won't have you distracting me with your inane chatter. Leave me be." <<He>> makes a dismissive gesture,
			<<else>>
				frowns <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `at you, brows furrowing,` : `a little`>> as you approach.

				"I'm a bit busy at the moment, <<pcpetname "Avery">>," <<he>> says before you can say anything. "Tending my garden takes focus<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("garden")>>, as I'm sure you know<</if>>, so I can't spend any more time on <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `listening to you natter on` : `chatting`>>. And I'm sure you have more important things to do, anyway." <<He>>
			<</if>>
		then goes back to <<his>> pruning.
		<</if>>
		<br><br>

		You shouldn't bother Avery anymore for today.
		<br><br>
		<<getouticon>><<link [[Leave Avery be|Mansion Talk Leave]]>><</link>>
	<</if>>

<<elseif $daily.avery.talk.count gte 3>>
	<<set $daily.avery.talk.ignore to true>>
	<<if $avery_mansion.schedule is "sleep">>
		Avery glares at you. "Leave me the fuck alone," <<he>> <<= either(`growls`,`hisses`)>>. "I'm trying to sleep."
	<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
		Avery glares at you. "Leave me the fuck alone," <<he>> <<= either(`growls`,`hisses`)>>. "You might have nothing to do, but time is money, and I'm trying to <<= $avery_mansion.schedule is "dinner" ? `eat` : $avery_mansion.schedule is "bath" ? `bathe` : $avery_mansion.schedule is "pool" ? `exercise` : `unwind`>> in peace."
	<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
		Avery's brows furrow, and <<his>> lip curls. "I'm not here to entertain your pestering, <<girl>>. Find something else to amuse yourself with."
	<<else>>
		Avery's brows twitch inward. "I'm sorry if you're bored, <<pcpetname "Avery">>. But I'd rather you find something other than this little game to amuse yourself with."
	<</if>>
	<<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
	<br><br>
	<<He>>
	<<if $avery_mansion.schedule is "bath">>
		looks away, ignoring you.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "sleep">>
		rolls over and covers <<his>> head with <<his>> blanket.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "breakfast">>
		looks away, taking a bite of <<his>> breakfast and ignoring you.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "study">>
		looks down at <<his>> book, ignoring you.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "pool">>
		goes back to <<= $avery_pool is "coffee" ? `scrolling through <<his>> phone` : $avery_pool is "sunbathe" ? `sunbathing` : `swimming laps`>>.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "garden">>
		looks back to the bush <<he>> was trimming, ignoring you.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "lounge">>
		looks away, ignoring you. You leave <<him>> be.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "drink">>
		takes a deep swig of <<his>> drink, looking away and ignoring you.
	<<else>>
		looks away, ignoring you.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
	<<getouticon>><<link [[Leave|Mansion Talk Leave]]>><</link>>

<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "sleep">>
	<<set $daily.avery.talk.annoyed += 1>>
	Avery appears to be asleep.
	<br><br>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"Avery?" you whisper, barely audible.
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"Hey, Avery," you say, at normal volume.
	<<else>>
		"Hey, Avery?" you whisper.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
	<<He>> opens <<his>> eyes and glares at you. "Leave me<<if $averyragerevealed gte 1>> the fuck<</if>> alone," <<he>> <<= either(`growls`,`hisses`)>>. "I'm trying to sleep." With that, <<he>> rolls over<<if $daily.avery.talk.annoyed gte 1>> again<</if>> and buries <<his>> face into <<his>> pillow. <<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
	<br><br>
	You shouldn't bother Avery while <<hes>> sleeping.
	<br><br>
	<<getouticon>><<link [[Leave Avery be|Mansion Talk Leave]]>><</link>>

<<else>>

	<<if $avery_mansion.schedule is "drink">>
		Avery watches you over the rim of <<his>> glass.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "pool" and $avery_pool is "swim">>
		Avery acknowledges you with a glance, then keeps swimming.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "garden">>
		Avery focuses on trimming the bush in front of <<him>>.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "lounge">>
		Avery reclines on the sofa, <<his>> arms outstretched.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "study">>
		Avery thumbs through the pages of the book in front of <<him>>.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "bath">>
		Avery reclines in the bath, and regards you.
	<<else>>
		Avery acknowledges your presence with a glance.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	/* Always here */
	<<socialiseicon>><<link [[Chat (0:15)|Mansion Talk Chat]]>><<set $daily.avery.talk.chat += 1>><</link>>

	/*
	<<if isLoveInterest("Avery") and !$daily.avery.talk.flirt and $avery_pool isnot "swim">>
		<br>
		<<brothelicon>><<link [[Flirt (0:15)|Mansion Talk Flirt]]>><<set $daily.avery.talk.chat += 1>><<set $daily.avery.talk.flirt to true>><</link>><<promiscuous1>>
	<</if>>
	<<if !$daily.avery.seduce>>
		<br>
		<<ind>><<link [[Seduce|Mansion Talk Seduce]]>><<set $daily.avery.talk.seduce to true>><</link>><<promiscuous2>>
	<</if>>
	 */
	<<if !$avery_mansion.study_unlocked>>
		<br>
		<<socialiseicon>><<link [[Ask to enter the study|Mansion Talk Study]]>><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>
	<<if $avery_mansion.assault_pair is 1>>
		<br>
		<<socialiseicon "breakdown">><<link [[Consider telling Avery you were assaulted in a spare room|Mansion Talk Assault]]>><<stress 6>><</link>><<gstress>>
		<br>
	<</if>>

	/* Questions */
	<<if $scienceproject is "ongoing">>
		<<scienceprojectchance>> /* Necessary to set the stats being compared against for the dialogue option */
		<<if ($sciencephalluschance gte 1 or $sciencelichenchance gte 1 or $scienceshroomchance gte 1) and !$avery_mansion?.attend.science>>
			<br>
			<<scienceicon>><<link [[Invite <<him>> to the science fair|Mansion Talk Ask]]>><<set $avery_ask to "science">><</link>>
			<br>
		<</if>>
	<</if>>
	<<if $mathsproject is "ongoing" and $mathschance gte 1 and !$avery_mansion?.attend.maths>>
		<br>
		<<mathicon>><<link [[Invite <<him>> to the maths competition|Mansion Talk Ask]]>><<set $avery_ask to "maths">><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>

	<<if $englishPlay is "ongoing" and $englishPlayReadiness gte 1 and !$avery_mansion?.attend.english_play>>
		<br>
		<<englishicon>><<link [[Invite <<him>> to come watch your school play|Mansion Talk Ask]]>><<set $avery_ask to "english_play">><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>

	<<if $avery_mansion_rent_confront is 1>>
		<br>
		<<socialiseicon "ask">><<link [[Ask Avery why <<he>> stopped paying Bailey|Mansion Talk Ask]]>><<set $avery_mansion_rent_confront to 2>><<set $avery_ask to "bailey">><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>
	<<if $avery_fate is "saved" and ["fresh", "sling", "cast", "healing"].includes($avery_mansion.injury_stage)>>
		<br>
		<<socialiseicon "ask">><<link [[Ask Avery how <<his>> arm is doing|Mansion Talk Ask]]>><<set $avery_ask to "injury">><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>

	<<if $avery_valentines and $avery_valentines.invite is true and $avery_valentines.reservations is false>>
		<<socialiseicon "ask">><<link [[Ask how Avery got dinner reservations on such short notice|Mansion Talk Ask]]>><<set $avery_valentines.reservations to true>><<set $avery_ask to "reservations">><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>

	<<if $avery_valentines and $avery_valentines.init is true and $avery_valentines.invite is false>>
		<<socialiseicon "ask">><<link [[Ask to go to dinner with Avery on Valentine's Day after all|Mansion Talk Ask]]>><<set $avery_ask to "valentines">><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>

	<<if $avery_valentines and $avery_valentines.chocolate is true and !$avery_valentines.chocolate_asked>>
		<<socialiseicon "ask">><<link [[Ask if Avery ate the chocolate you gave <<him>>|Mansion Talk Ask]]>><<set $avery_ask to "chocolate">><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>

	<br>

	<<getouticon>><<link [[Leave Avery be|Mansion Talk Leave]]>><<set $daily.avery.talk.annoyed += 1>><</link>>
	<br>

<</if>>


:: Mansion Talk Ask
<<effects>>

<<if $avery_ask is "science" or $avery_ask is "maths" or $avery_ask is "english_play">>
	<<if $avery_ask is "science">>
		<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
			"I just," you say, straightening your back. "I was wondering if you would like to come see my project at the science fair?
			<<if $averySeen.includes("meetPark")>> The one that you helped me with?<</if>> I-if you have the time, that is," you add. "It'll be at the town hall."
		<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
			"I've got a science fair project I'm going to be showing at the town hall. <<if $averySeen.includes("meetPark")>>Remember that lichen on that statue in the park? That one. <</if>>Just letting you know in case you want to come see it," you say with a shrug.
		<<else>>
			"<<if $averySeen.includes("meetPark")>>Remember that lichen I was trying to get in the park? Well, <</if>>I've been working on a science project for the fair at the town hall coming up, and I was wondering if you'd like to come see the results," you say with a smile.<<if $averySeen.includes("meetPark")>> "Since you helped me with it."<</if>>
		<</if>>
	<<elseif $avery_ask is "maths">>
		<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
			"Well, um," you say, straightening your back. "I was wondering if you would like to come see me at the upcoming maths competition? I-if you have the time, that is," you add. "It'll be at the town hall."
		<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
			"There's a maths competition I might be trying at soon. It'll be over in the town hall. Just letting you know in case you want to come see me there," you say with a shrug.
		<<else>>
			"There's a maths competition happening at the town hall soon. I thought I might participate in it. If I do, would you like to come watch?" you say with a smile.
		<</if>>
	<<elseif $avery_ask is "english_play">>
		<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
			"Actually," you say, straightening your back. "I was wondering if you would like to come see my performance at the upcoming school play? I-if you have time, that is," you add. "It'll be at the town hall."
		<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
			"I've got this play I signed up for that'll be showing at the town hall soon. Just letting you know in case you want to come watch my brilliant performance," you say with a smirk.
		<<else>>
			"I signed up for a school play that will be showing at town hall coming up. I was wondering if you'd like to come see my performance," you say with a smile.
		<</if>>
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	Avery
	<<if C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
		<<if $averyragerevealed is 1>>
			looks irritated at your request. "<span class="red">I don't have time to waste</span> on something as frivolous as that." <<He>> scoffs.
		<<else>>
			raises an eyebrow. "I'm afraid that <span class="red">I don't have time to spare</span> on something like that, <<pcpetname "Avery">>." <<He>> sighs.
		<</if>>
		"And for the record, I don't know why you're bothering with it either, considering you don't even seem to have the time to
		<<avery_mansion_housework_total>>
		<<if $avery_mansion.rage.assess gte 9>>
			do anything I've asked of you,"
		<<elseif _avery_mansion_housework_total gte 6>>
			clean the house,"
		<<elseif $avery_mansion.rage.dinner_missed gte 1 and $averyragerevealed is 1>>
			do something as simple as make dinner,"
		<<else>>
			spend on <i>me</i>,"
		<</if>>
		<<he>> <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `mutters darkly` : `says coolly`>>.
		<br><br>
	<<elseif C.npc.Avery.love lt 50>>
		raises an eyebrow. "I'm afraid <span class="red">I can't make time</span> for something like that," <<he>> says.
		<<if $averyragerevealed is 1>>
			"I'm far too busy, as you should know." <<He>> returns <<his>> attention to what <<he>> was doing. "But good luck, <<pcpetname "Avery">>.<<if C.npc.Avery.rage gte 40>> You're going to need it.<</if>>"
		<<else>>
			"I've been quite busy, with work and everything else." <<He>> returns <<his>> attention to what <<he>> was doing. "But good luck, <<pcpetname "Avery">>."
		<</if>>
		<br><br>
	<<else>>
		hums. "A <<= $avery_ask is "science" ? `science fair` : $avery_ask is "maths" ? `maths competition` : `play`>>, is it?" <<He>>
		<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
			stares at you with a scrutinising look for a long few moments. Then <<he>> smiles. "<span class="green">Why not?</span> I expect to be impressed. Don't let me down, <<pcpetname "Avery">>.
		<<else>>
			smiles. "<span class="green">I don't see why not.</span> I look forward to being impressed, <<pcpetname "Avery">>.
		<</if>>
		Now, the town hall, you said?"
		<br><br>
		You tell <<him>> the details, such as the date and
		<<if $avery_ask is "science">>
			<<set $avery_mansion.attend.science to true>>
			what your project entails. You go over the details of your
			<<if $scienceshroomchance>>
				mushroom project.
			<<elseif $sciencephalluschance>>
				phallus project.
				<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
					<<He>> gives you a stern look. "You ought to work on a different project. You wouldn't want to give anyone the wrong idea, would you?"
				<<elseif C.npc.Avery.dom gte 40>>
					<<He>> raises an eyebrow. "You should work on a different project. After all, <<= $NPCList[0].penis isnot "none" ? `mine ought to be the only one you're 'studying,'" <<he>> says with a perverse smile.` : `you wouldn't want to give anyone the wrong idea, would you?"`>>
				<<else>>
					<<He>> gives you a hard to read look. "I do hope you haven't selected that project for," <<he>> pauses. "recreational purposes."
				<</if>>
			<<else>>
				lichen project<<if $averySeen.includes("meetPark") and $sciencelichenpark gte 1>>, and what you learned about the lichen <<he>> helped you with<</if>>.
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif $avery_ask is "maths">>
			<<set $avery_mansion.attend.maths to true>>
			the complex maths problem that you're being asked to solve. You
			<<if $mathschance gte 50>>
				attempt to explain what you can about your solution.
			<<else>>
				do your best to explain what you can about your <<= $mathschance lte 10 ? `theories, though you haven't really gotten started yet` : `solution`>>.
			<</if>>
			Though Avery makes acknowledging sounds and nods at all the right times, you suspect
			<<if $mathschance gte 75>>
				some of it flies completely over <<his>> head.
			<<elseif $mathschance gte 50>>
				that <<he>> would be unable to help you even if you asked.
			<<else>>
				<<he>> finds it as perplexing as you do.
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<else>>
			<<set $avery_mansion.attend.english_play to true>>
			what role you'll be playing in the play. <<He>>
			<<if $englishPlayRoles.Player is "Cass">>
				comments that your chosen role suits you, and that <<he>> looks forward to seeing you on stage.
			<<elseif $englishPlayRoles.Player is "Taylor">>
				says that Cass would have been a more fitting role for you, but that <<he>> looks forward to seeing you on stage.
			<<else>>
				seems to be caught off guard by your chosen role. <<He>> <<= $averyragerevealed gte 1 ? `muses that it's quite bold of you to choose such a role, and that you should have chosen Cass instead` : `tells you <<hes>> curious to see how you pull it off, though Cass would have been a more suitable role for you`>> .
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<</if>>
	<</if>>

<<elseif $avery_ask is "bailey">>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"Um," you say, staring at the <<= $outside is 1 ? `ground` : `floor`>>. "Bailey told me that you've stopped p-paying <<nnpc_him "Bailey">>?" You can't bring yourself to ask why.
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"Hey, why'd you stop paying Bailey?" you demand. "<<nnpc_He "Bailey">> started asking me for money again."
	<<else>>
		"I heard from Bailey that you stopped paying <<nnpc_him "Bailey">>," you say, trying not to sound accusatory. "Did I do something wrong?"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
	Avery frowns and
	<<if $averySeen.includes("chase")>>
		narrows <<his>> eyes at you.
	<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1>>
		raises an eyebrow at you.
	<<else>> /* Rage concealed */
		sighs.
	<</if>>
	"<<= either(`You want to know why`,`Do you really have to ask`)>>? Well,
	<<if $avery_mansion.rage.assess gte 9>> /* Avery's demands */
		I don't know if you've forgotten, or if it was on purpose<<if $averyragerevealed gte 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>> just to spite me<</if>>, but <span class="pink">I do expect you to do as I request of you</span>."
	<<else>> /* PC is missing for more than one day */
		I <span class="pink">hadn't seen you in days</span>. What else did you expect?"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
	<<He>> <<= $avery_mansion.injury_stage is "sling" or $avery_pool is "swim" ? `huffs` : `crosses <<his>> arms`>>. "I don't ask for much of you. But if you can't keep track of your responsibilities here, then I presume you are prioritising your responsibilities elsewhere. In which case, I'm sure that you can pay Bailey yourself."
	<br><br>
	Without a second look, Avery returns to what <<he>> was doing.
	<br><br>

<<elseif $avery_ask is "injury">>
	<<if $avery_mansion.injury_stage isnot "healing">> /* Avery is still in a cast */

		<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
			"I just wanted to know how your arm is doing. Is there anything I can do to help?" you ask.
		<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
			"How's the arm?" you ask. "Need help with anything?"
		<<else>>
			"How is your arm doing?" you ask, peering at it. "If you need help with anything, let me know."
		<</if>>
		<br><br>
		<<if $avery_mansion.injury_stage is "fresh">> /* Cast in a sling */
			<<set $avery_mansion.injury_stage to "fresh_done">>
			Avery <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `scoffs` : `sighs`>>. "I appreciate the offer, <<pcpetname "Avery">>, but rest assured I can take care of
			<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
				myself." Then <<his>> lip curls. "If you want to help, however, you could do so by doing as you're told. Then I'd have one less thing to trouble myself over."
			<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
				myself." Then <<he>> grimaces. "Taking care of <<= $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("lounge") ? `the cooking and cleaning` : `dinner`>> is enough. Though, if you want to help, then I'd appreciate more <<= $avery_mansion.rage.dinner_missed gte 1 ? `consistency with my meals` : `obedience from you`>>."
			<<else>>
				myself. Taking care of <<= $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("lounge") ? `the cooking and cleaning` : `dinner`>> is enough."
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif $avery_mansion.injury_stage is "sling">> /* Only wearing cast */
			<<set $avery_mansion.injury_stage to "sling_done">>
			Avery shakes <<his>> head. "Now that I don't have to wear the sling anymore, things are easier. Though," <<He>> <<= $averyragerevealed gte 1 ? `glares` : `frowns`>> at <<his>> cast. "This<<if $averyragerevealed gte 1>> bloody<</if>> thing is still a

			<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
				nuisance." Then <<he>> glowers at you. "Now that I think about it, if you wanted to help me, <<pcpetname "Avery">>, just do as you're told. Then I'd have one less thing to trouble myself with."
			<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
				nuisance." Then <<he>> looks back at you. "As long as you take care of <<= $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("lounge") ? `the cooking and cleaning` : `dinner`>>, that's enough. Though if you want to help, I'd appreciate more <<= $avery_mansion.rage.dinner_missed gte 1 ? `consistency with my meals` : `obedience from you`>>."
			<<else>>
				nuisance. Taking care of <<= $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("lounge") ? `the cooking and cleaning` : `dinner`>> is enough, <<pcpetname "Avery">>," <<he>> says, giving you a tired smile.
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<else>> /* Only two weeks of recovery left */
			<<set $avery_mansion.injury_stage to "cast_done">>
			Avery shakes <<his>> head. "I've gotten quite used to wearing a cast," <<he>> smiles. "Though it's not long until I'll be having it off. <<= $avery_mansion.injury_timer>> days from now. It can't come soon enough."
			<br><br>
			<span class="gold"><i>Once Avery's cast is removed, <<he>> will regain use of both hands in encounters.</i></span>
			<br><br>
		<</if>>

	<<else>> /* Avery has fully recovered */
		<<set $avery_mansion.injury_stage to "healed">>
		<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
			"How is your arm doing, Avery?" you ask. "Now that it's out of the cast, I mean." You give <<him>> a small smile. "Better, I hope?"
		<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
			"So, you're finally free from your cast," you say, pointing at <<his>> right arm. "How's it feel?"
		<<else>>
			"Your arm looks better," you say. "How are you feeling now that you don't have to wear the cast anymore?"
		<</if>>
		<br><br>
		Avery smiles,
		<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 80>>
			a dangerous tilt to it. "It feels better. Much better," <<he>> says, flexing the fingers of <<his>> right hand. "Broken bones heal stronger," <<he>> murmurs, almost to <<himself>>. Then <<he>> reaches over to pinch your cheek with <<his>> now freed hand. It hurts a little, and <<he>> smirks when you flinch. <<pain 1>><<gpain>>

		<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 40>>
			looking pleased. "I do feel much better," <<he>> says, flexing the fingers of <<his>> right hand. "It really was quite frustrating, having to wear that horrid thing. But it's in the past now." <<He>> reaches over to pinch your cheek with <<his>> now freed hand. "How sweet of you to ask, <<pcpetname "Avery">>."

		<<else>>
			looking pleased. "I do feel much better," <<he>> says. <<He>> flexes the fingers of <<his>> right hand. "It was quite the trial, and yet I've overcome it, and stronger than ever." <<He>> <<laughs>> quietly, and reaches over to stroke your cheek with <<his>> now freed hand. "Thank you for asking, <<pcpetname "Avery">>."
		<</if>>
		<br><br>
	<</if>>

<<elseif $avery_ask is "reservations">>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"Um, Avery? I've been curious. How did you get those reservations so short notice?" you ask. "I've heard you have to wait a year for that restaurant."
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"Hey, how did you get those reservations in only a couple weeks?" you ask. "You have to wait a year for that place."
	<<else>>
		"How did you get those reservations on such short notice?" you ask. "Don't you have to wait a year for that restaurant?"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	Avery smiles
	<<if $avery_fate is "ascended">>
		smugly. "For others, that's true." <<He>> <<laughs>>. "But queues don't apply to me, <<pcpetname "Avery">>. You'd do well to remember that."
		<br><br>
		<<= $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60 ? "There's a slight threat in <<his>> tone." : "<<He>> gives you a wink.">>
		<br><br>
	<<else>>
		mysteriously. "Ah, well... It's useful knowing the right kind of people." <<He>> hums. "But I'd prefer you think about how excited you are for it, <<pcpetname "Avery">>, rather than how it came to be."
		<br><br>
	<</if>>
<<elseif $avery_ask is "valentines">>
	You ask Avery if <<he>> still has those reservations, and tell <<him>> you want to go to dinner after all.
	<br><br>
	<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
		Avery scowls at you<<if $avery_mansion.injury_stage isnot "sling">> as <<he>> crosses <<his>> arms<</if>>. "When you haven't even apologised for turning me down in the first place?" <<He>> scoffs. "Why don't you try asking again, properly this time?"
		<br><br>
	<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
		Avery sneers at you. "Bold of you to ask such a thing after turning me down in the first place. You haven't even apologised to me for it." <<He>> sniffs, offended. "But if you apologise now, then I'll consider it."
		<br><br>
	<<else>>
		Avery frowns at you. "You changed your mind, have you?" <<He>> hums thoughtfully. "I would still like to take you, but I would appreciate an apology for the way you turned me down before."
		<br><br>
	<</if>>
	<<set _skip_end_links to true>>
	<<link [[Apologise|Mansion Talk Ask Apologise]]>><<set $avery_valentines.invite to true>><</link>>
	<br>
	<<link [[Don't apologise|Mansion Talk Ask Apologise Refuse]]>><</link>>
	<br>


<<elseif $avery_ask is "chocolate">>
	<<set $avery_valentines.chocolate_asked to true>>
	You ask Avery if <<he>> ate the chocolate you made for <<him>>.
	<br><br>
	"I did," <<he>> says with a nod. "I saved it for a stressful day at work, and it did just the job. Thank you, <<pcpetname "Avery">>." <<He>> <<= C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60 ? "smirks" : "smiles">> at you<<if C.npc.Avery.love gte 60>> and gives you a pat on the head<</if>>.<<if isLoveInterest("Avery") or $averyromance>> You can't help but smile.<<stress -3>><<lstress>><</if>>
	<br><br>
<</if>>

<<if !_skip_end_links>>
	<<endevent>>
	<<avery_mansion_end_links>>
<</if>>

:: Mansion Talk Chat
<<effects>>

<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
	"I just wanted to talk a little," you say. "If that's okay."
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"Just wanted to chat," you say.
<<else>>
	"I just wanted to chat for a bit," you say. "If you have the time."
<</if>>
<br><br>
<<if C.npc.Avery.rage gte 80 or C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20 and $avery_mansion.rage.assess gte 1>>
	<<avery_current_room_dirty_check>>
	Avery <<= $averyragerevealed gte 1 ? `sneers` : `frowns`>> at you. "I'm sure you have better things to be doing, <<pcpetname "Avery">>," <<he>> says<<if _dirty_room>>, pointedly<</if>>.

	<<He>>
	<<if $avery_mansion.schedule is "bath">>
		looks away, ignoring you.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "sleep">>
		rolls over and covers <<his>> head with <<his>> blanket.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "breakfast">>
		looks away, taking a bite of <<his>> breakfast and ignoring you.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "study">>
		looks down at <<his>> book, ignoring you.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "pool">>
		goes back to <<= $avery_pool is "coffee" ? `scrolling through <<his>> phone` : $avery_pool is "sunbathe" ? `sunbathing` : `swimming laps`>>.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "garden">>
		looks back to the bush <<he>> was trimming, ignoring you.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "lounge">>
		looks away, ignoring you. You leave <<him>> be.
	<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "drink">>
		takes a deep swig of <<his>> drink, looking away and ignoring you.
	<<else>>
		looks away, ignoring you.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
	<<endevent>>
	<<avery_mansion_end_links>>
<<else>>
	Avery glances at <<his>> watch.
	<<if Time.hour is 23 and Time.minute gte 45>>
		"Afraid not. I'm going to bed soon." <<He>> looks back at you. "Another time, perhaps."
		<br><br>
		<<endevent>>
		<<avery_mansion_end_links>>
	<<else>>
		<<He>> hums, and looks back at you. "Very well.<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>> So long as you don't waste my time.<</if>>"
		<br><br>
		<<link [[Next|Mansion Talk Chat 2]]>><<pass 15>><</link>>
	<</if>>
<</if>>

:: Mansion Talk Chat 2
<<effects>>

<<set _chat to {}>>

You sit beside Avery, and the two of you chat a while.
<<if $avery_mansion.schedule is "drink">>
	<<He>> always seems to have a drink in <<his>> hand.
<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "pool">>
	<<if $avery_pool is "coffee">>
		<<His>> phone is set aside for now, and <<he>> sips at <<his>> coffee.
	<<elseif $avery_pool is "sunbathe">>
		<<He>> doesn't shift positions much.
	<<else>>
		<<He>> climbs up to sit beside you on the lip of the pool, legs dangling in the water as you talk.
	<</if>>
<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "garden">>
	<<He>> takes a break from <<his>> gardening, and sits on a nearby bench with you as you talk.
<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "lounge">>
	<<He>> hasn't turned the television off, but it's been muted.
<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "study">>
	<<He>> doesn't set aside <<his>> book, but <<he>> shuts it with finger marking <<his>> place.
<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "bath">>
	<<His>> eyes close, but <<he>> stays engaged in the conversation.
<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "breakfast">>
	<<He>> doesn't stop eating <<his>> breakfast, but never speaks when <<his>> mouth is full.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<set _chat.topic to random(1,7)>>



<<if _chat.topic is 1 and $avery_tower.intro>> /* Avery's skyscraper */
	<<if $avery_fate is "ascended" or $avery_fate is "saved">>
		<<if $avery_fate is "ascended">>
			<<He>> seems pleased with <<himself>> today. More than once as you talk, <<he>> <<= either(
			`humbly brags about treating a host of influential individuals from outside of town`,
			`boasts about being invited to twice the amount of parties than <<he>> used to be`,
			`"complains" about how difficult it is to manage all the responsibilities that come with such high levels of prestige`
			)>>, wearing a <<= either(`self-satisfied`,`smug`,`haughty`)>> smile the entire time.
		<<else>>
			<<He>> seems distracted today. More than once as you talk, you notice <<him>> <<= $outside is 1 ? `glance over in the direction of Elk Street` : $avery_mansion.schedule is "drink" ? `draining <<his>> drinks faster than usual` : `staring into the distance`>> with a <<= either(`frustrated`,`tired`,`difficult to read`)>> expression.
		<</if>>
		<br><br>
	<<elseif $avery_tower.progress gte 25 and $avery_tower.stage is 1>>
		You ask about the person you met underneath the foundation of Avery's skyscraper.
		<br><br>
		"Ah, don't worry, <<pcpetname "Avery">>," <<he>> says, giving you an indulgent smile. "You have nothing to fear. We increased security around the construction site, so nothing like that will happen again."
		<br><br>
		It's not what you were asking about, but you don't push the subject.
		<br><br>
	<<elseif $avery_tower.progress gte 60 and $avery_tower.stage is 2 and $averySeen.includes("whitney_crash")>>
		You ask if Avery ever got <<his>> car fixed. A dark look comes over <<his>> face at the question.
		<br><br>
		"I did," <<he>> answers. <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `"Despite that brat's` : `<<He>> smooths <<his>> expression over. "Despite that <<nnpc_gendery "Whitney">>'s`>> best efforts, it managed to survive the accident." <<He>> talks about <<his>> car like it's a living being.
		<br><br>
	<<else>>
		<<= either(`You ask how Avery's skyscraper is shaping up.`,`Avery's skyscraper comes up during the course of the conversation.`)>>

		<<He>>
		<<if $avery_tower.stage is 2>>
			grins. "It's all complete. I believe they're working on finishing touches. Landscaping and the like, but it's just about ready for its grand opening at the end of the month." <<He>> puts <<his>> hand on your shoulder. "I can't wait to show it to you," <<he>> murmurs. <<His>> gaze on you is more intent than usual.
			<br><br>
		<<else>> /* In progress */
			<<if $avery_tower.progress gte 80>>
				seems pleased with the skyscraper's current progress. <<avery_mansion_skyscraper_week_estimate>> <<if C.npc.Avery.rage lt 60>> <<He>> praises your skill as a fellow <<= $player.gender_appearance is "m" ? `host` : `hostess`>>.<</if>> <<npcincr Avery rage -1>><<larage>>
				<br><br>
			<<elseif $avery_tower.progress gte 60>>
				seems content with the skyscraper's current progress. <<avery_mansion_skyscraper_week_estimate>> <<if C.npc.Avery.rage lt 40>> <<He>> praises your skill as a fellow <<= $player.gender_appearance is "m" ? `host` : `hostess`>>.<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<<elseif $avery_tower.progress gte 40>>
				seems impatient with the skyscraper's current progress. The construction is proceeding steadily, but it could be going much faster.<<if C.npc.Avery.rage gte 80>> <<He>> informs you <<he>> expects more from you going forward.<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<<elseif $avery_tower.progress gte 20>>
				seems <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `irritated` : `disgruntled`>> by the skyscraper's current progress.<<if C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>> <<He>> informs you <<he>> expects better from you going forward.<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<<else>>
				seems <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `furious` : `irritated`>> by the skyscraper's current progress.<<if C.npc.Avery.rage gte 40>> <<He>> informs you <<he>> expects better from you going forward.<</if>> <<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
				<br><br>
			<</if>>
		<</if>>
	<</if>>

	<<endevent>>
	<<avery_mansion_end_links>>

<<elseif _chat.topic is 2>> /* PC's possible occupations (including temple) */
	<<set _avery_rng to random(1, 5)>>
	<<if _avery_rng is 1 and $chef_state gte 3>> /* Cafe */
		<<if $chef_state gte 9>>
			<<rng 1 3>>
			<<if $rng is 1 and $chef_speech isnot "truth" and !$avery_ocean_breeze_comment>>
				<<set $avery_ocean_breeze_comment to 1>>
				The day of the Ocean Breeze Cafe's reopening comes up. "Was that the first time you've ever been asked to give a speech before?" Avery asks. <<He>> goes on to give you advice about public speaking.
				<<if $englishtrait gte 3>>
					It's nothing you didn't know already, but you let <<him>> go on.
				<<else>>
					<span class="green">It's helpful advice</span>—<<he>> knows what <<hes>> about. <<englishskill>><<genglish>>
				<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<<elseif $rng is 2 and !$avery_ocean_breeze_comment and $chef_avery>>
				<<set $avery_ocean_breeze_comment to 1>>
				The day of the Ocean Breeze Cafe's reopening comes up. "Was that the first time you've ever walked down a red carpet?" Avery asks. "It's exciting, isn't it? What a shame your old caretaker had to go and ruin the mood." <<= $averyragerevealed is 1? `<<He>> scoffs` : `<<His>> smile twitches`>> at the memory. "I might have stayed longer, but I only had so much time to spare."
				<br><br>
			<<else>>
				"I've seen you on advertisements for the Ocean Breeze Cafe," <<he>> says. "You look <<cute>> all dressed up. You're a <<= $photo and $photo.audienceSize gte 2 ? `professional` : `natural`>> in front of a camera, aren't you?" <<He>> smiles at you. "Have you considered making a career of it?"
				<br><br>
			<</if>>
		<<else>>
			"I've heard good things about the deluxe cream buns at the Ocean Breeze Cafe," <<he>> says when the topic of cuisine comes up. "'World-class,' they say. I have to admit, with a reputation like that, I'm a little curious to try them myself at some point."
			<br><br>
		<</if>>

	<<elseif _avery_rng is 2 and ($temple_rank is "prospective" or $temple_rank is "initiate" or $temple_rank is "monk" or $temple_rank is "priest")>> /* Temple */
		<<if $temple_rank is "prospective" and !$averySeen.includes("temple_told")>>
			<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("temple_prospective")>>
			You tell Avery that you've been invited to join the temple as an initiate.<<if C.npc.Sydney.init is 1>> You mention that a fellow student that has joined as well.<</if>>
			<br><br>
			Avery
			<<if $averyragerevealed gte 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
				rolls <<his>> eyes. "Working with the temple? You?" <<He>> huffs a laugh. "You hate spending time around here that badly?<<if !$avery_fate and $avery_party?.jordan_init>> I suppose you would be united in defying me.<</if>>"
				<br><br>
			<<else>>
				frowns. "I don't know about that, <<pcpetname "Avery">>. It's quite a demanding position, isn't it? And so much work for no pay." <<He>> shakes <<his>> head.
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

			<<He>> pauses for a moment, then gives you a sly smile. "You know," <<he>> drawls, "on second thought, why don't you give it a try?
			<<if $averyragerevealed gte 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
				Perhaps you'd learn a little discipline."
			<<elseif $averyragerevealed gte 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
				You might learn a thing or two about behaving yourself."
			<<else>>
				Who knows? You might learn something interesting there."
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif $temple_rank is "initiate" or $temple_rank is "monk" or $temple_rank is "priest">>
			<<if !$averySeen.includes("temple_initiate")>>
				<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("temple_initiate")>>
				The temple comes up during your conversation, and
				<<if $averySeen.includes("temple_prospective")>>
					Avery asks if you decided to join the temple's ranks after all, <<= $averyragerevealed gte 1 ? `an impish` : `a`>> smile on <<his>> lips. You tell <<him>> you did, and that smile widens a little. "Very good," <<he>> says. "It's
				<<else>>
					you mention that you're a <<temple_title>>. At first, <<he>> appears displeased by the news, but after a few moments of thought, <<he>> dons an impish smile. "Well, I suppose it is
				<</if>>
				important to have extracurriculars at your age."
				<br><br>
				<<He>> then reminds you that you still have your <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `responsibilities here in the mansion` : `other responsibilities`>> to take care of.
				<br><br>
			<<elseif $player.virginity.temple is "Avery">>
				You confess that you haven't yet told the temple of your broken vow. Avery seems far less concerned about it than you.<<if $averyragerevealed gte 1>> <<He>> appears to be more entertained than anything.<</if>>
				<br><br>
				"Couldn't you keep it a secret?" <<he>> suggests. You tell <<him>> about the chastity exam, and <<he>> <<= $averyragerevealed gte 1 ? `<<laughs>>` : `gives a wry smile`>>. "Being a <<temple_title>> sounds quite complicated. My poor<<if C.npc.Avery.love gte 30>> little<</if>> doll."
				<br><br>
			<<else>>
				<<rng 1 3>>
				You talk to Avery about working as a <<temple_title>>.

				<<if $rng is 1 and !$avery_fate and $avery_party?.jordan_init and $avery_tower.effects.includes("temple")>>
					<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
						<<His>> lips twist with distaste. "Could you tell the rest of your ilk to back off from my skyscraper?
					<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
						<<He>> raises an eyebrow. "I suppose you couldn't just tell Jordan and the rest of your <i><<nnpc_his "Jordan">></i>> ilk to leave my skyscraper be?
					<<else>>
						<<His>> smile becomes strained. "Speaking of the temple, do you think you might tell Jordan and <<nnpc_his "Jordan">> followers to leave my skyscraper be?
					<</if>>
					It would save us all some hassle."
					<br><br>
				<<elseif $rng is 2 and !$avery_fate and ($player.virginity.vaginal is true or $player.virginity.penile is true) and $player.virginity.temple is true and !$averySeen.includes("player_virgin")>>
					<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("player_virgin")>>
					<<if $worn.genitals.type.includes("chastity")>>
						Avery <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `rolls <<his>> eyes` : `sighs`>>. "That must be why you wear that chastity belt." <<He>> puts a hand on the small of your back. "I still think it's overcaution on your part."
					<<else>>
						Avery raises an eyebrow. "A <<temple_title>>, hm?" At first, <<he>>
						<<if $averyragerevealed gte 1>>
							seems uninterested, but then something seems to occur to <<him>>. "I presume you've taken the vow of chastity, too, then?" <<He>> hums, and a smirk comes to <<his>> lips.
						<<else>>
							hums. "You have to take a vow of chastity to join the temple's ranks, don't you?"
						<</if>> <<npcincr Avery lust 1>><<glust>>
						<br><br>
						For the rest of the conversation, you notice Avery giving you heated and lingering looks every now and then.
					<</if>>
					<br><br>
				<<else>>
					"A <<temple_title>>." Avery
					<<if $averyragerevealed is 1>>
						raises an eyebrow. "To think someone <<= C.npc.Avery.rage gte 40 ? `so bratty` : `like you`>>
					<<else>>
						hums. "To think someone like you
					<</if>>
					is a member of the temple." <<He>> <<= C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20 ? `smirks` : `smiles`>>. "I wonder <<= C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20 ? `if you're as much of a handful for them as you are for me` : `what they think of us`>>?" <<he>> muses.
					<br><br>
				<</if>>
			<</if>>

		<<else>>
			The temple comes up during your conversation, and you chat about which of its teachings both of you follow. Avery tells you that <<he>> follows
			<<if $averyragerevealed is 1>>
				them in public, but not in private. "I'm far too busy to waste
			<<else>>
				the basic teachings as <<he>> must, but <<hes>> not very pious. "I'm a bit too busy to be spending so much of
			<</if>>
			my time on such things," <<he>> says.
			<br><br>
		<</if>>

	<<elseif _avery_rng is 3>> /* Spa */
		<<He>> mentions wanting to visit the spa again soon.
		<<if $averySeen.includes("spa")>>
			<<if $averySpaBanWeeks gte 1>>
				<<He>> gives you a <<= C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60 ? `dark` : C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20 ? `stern` : `sour`>> look. "If we meet there again, I hope you'll be more agreeable, <<pcpetname "Avery">>."
			<<else>>
				"It was nice seeing you there last time, <<pcpetname "Avery">>," <<he>> says. "Hopefully next time will be even better."<<if C.npc.Avery.love gte 80>> <<He>> winks.<</if>>
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif $spa_job gte 1 and !$averySeen.includes("spa")>>
			When you remark that it's odd you haven't seen Avery there, <<he>> says, "I only go on Sundays, when I can make the time. It's the only day I can make the time for it—before our dinner parties, of course."
			<br><br>
		<<else>> /* Player hook for the spa */
			"It is a nice place," <<he>> says. "Not far." <<He>> peers at you, and adds, "You might
			<<if $beauty gte ($beautymax / 7) * 6>>
				try your hand at working there, <<pcpetname "Avery">>. You've got the face<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>> and demeanour<</if>> for it."
			<<elseif currentSkillValue("handskill") gte 400>>
				try your hand at working there, <<pcpetname "Avery">>. You're quite skilled with your hands, after all."
			<<else>>
				visit yourself sometime. You could use it," <<he>> adds with a <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20 ? `snort` : `smile`>>.
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<</if>>

	<<elseif _avery_rng is 4>> /* Office */
		<<if $officejobintro gte 1 and !$averySeen.includes("officeAssistant")>>
			"I've been looking for a skilled personal assistant
			<<if $averySeen.includes("office")>>
				, and <<office_manager>> told me you'd be a good fit," <<he>> says. "I hope you're giving the offer the consideration that it's due?"
			<<else>>
				," <<he>> says, giving you a pointed look. "I'll have to ask <<office_manager>> if there are any skilled temps that could be trusted with the job."
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
			<<He>> smoothly transitions to another topic before you can say anything on the matter.
