<<elseif _chat.topic is 6 and $worn.neck.name is "love locket">> /* Love locket */
	During a lull in the conversation, Avery's eyes land on your love locket.
	<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
		<<He>> stares at it askance. "A locket? How unexpectedly sentimental of you."
	<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
		"A locket, hm?" <<He>> raises an eyebrow. "How charming."
	<<else>>
		"Is that a love locket?" <<he>> asks. "It looks cute on you."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
	<<link [[Thank <<him>>|Mansion Talk Chat Locket]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
	<br>

	<<neckstrip>><<set _colour to $carried.neck.colour>>
	<<wearProp "love locket" _colour>>

	<<if !$carried.neck.photo>>
		<<link [[Show <<him>> your love locket|Mansion Talk Chat Locket]]>><<set $phase to 3>><</link>>
		<br>
	<<else>>
		<<link [[Show <<him>> your love locket|Mansion Talk Chat Locket]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>
	<<link [[Change the subject|Mansion Talk Chat Locket]]>><<set $phase to 4>><</link>>
	<br>

<<else>> /* Misc */
	<<set _chat.misc to random(1,6)>>
	<<if _chat.misc is 1>> /* Grades */
		Avery brings up your school grades.
		<<if ($mathstrait + $sciencetrait + $englishtrait + $historytrait) gte 12>>
			You tell <<him>> how well you're doing. <<He>> seems pleased<<if C.npc.Avery.love gte 50>>, and pats you on the head<</if>>. <<stress -6>><<lstress>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif ($mathstrait + $sciencetrait + $englishtrait + $historytrait) lte 5>>
			Aware of how poorly you're doing, you change the subject. <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60 ? `Though <<he>> looks irritated at being ignored, <<he>>` : $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `<<He>> seems displeased by your obvious diversion, but` : `Likely picking up on the implication, <<he>>`>> doesn't push the subject. <<stress 6>><<gstress>>
			<br><br>
		<<else>>
			You tell <<him>> you're doing all right. <<He>> <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 40 ? `mutters about how you could be doing better, but` : $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `just seems glad you're not failing, and` : `hums noncommittally, and`>> moves on.
			<br><br>
		<</if>>
	<<elseif _chat.misc is 2>> /* PC's clothes */
		<<rng 1 2>>
		<<if $rng is 1 and ($avery_mansion.jobs.includes("maid") or $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("formal"))>>
			<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("maid")>>
				<<if ($worn.upper.type.includes("maid") and $worn.upper.femininity gte 1) or ($worn.lower.type.includes("maid") and $worn.lower.femininity gte 1) or ($worn.head.type.includes("maid") and $worn.head.femininity gte 1)>>
					<<He>> nods at your maid dress. "Now, that's what I like to see when I get home." <<He>> puts a hand on your thigh. "I know you aren't actually my maid, but you do look cute <<= $player.gender_appearance is "m" ? `in a dress, my boy`:`dressed as one`>>," <<he>> adds with a smile,
				<<elseif $worn.upper.type.includes("maid") or $worn.lower.type.includes("maid") or $worn.head.type.includes("maid")>>
					<<He>> nods at your revealing clothing. "Now, that's what I like to see when I get home." <<He>> puts a hand on your thigh. "I must say you look quite alluring dressed like this," <<he>> purrs,
				<<else>>
					<<He>> eyes you up and down. <<He>> <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `raises one brow` : `cocks <<his>> head`>> and says, "I look forward to seeing you in maid's attire next time I come home." It's a pointed statement. "I know you aren't actually my maid, but you would look cute <<= $player.gender_appearance is "m" ? `in a dress, my boy`:`dressed as one`>>," <<he>> adds with a smile,
				<</if>>
				leaning closer.
			<<else>> /* Formal */
				<<if $worn.upper.type.includes("formal") or $worn.lower.type.includes("formal")>>
					<<He>> nods at your
					<<if $worn.upper.type.includes("formal")>>
						<<print $worn.upper.name>>.
					<<else>>
						<<print $worn.lower.name>>.
					<</if>>
					"It's that style that I like seeing you in. You do look <<cute>> in it,
				<<else>>
					<<He>> eyes you up and down. <<He>> <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `raises one brow` : `cocks <<his>> head`>> and says, "I look forward to seeing you in formalwear more often." It's a pointed statement. "You look <<cute>> all dressed up for me,
				<</if>>
				you know," <<he>> adds with a smile, putting a hand on your thigh.
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<else>>
			<<outfitChecks>> /* Creates temporary variables that allow checking for _fullyNaked, see outfitChecks() */
			<<if $worn.upper.type.includes("formal") or $worn.lower.type.includes("formal")>>
				<<He>> smiles and nods at your
				<<if $worn.upper.type.includes("formal")>>
					<<print $worn.upper.name>>.
				<<else>>
					<<print $worn.lower.name>>.
				<</if>>
				"I do like seeing you in formalwear. It makes you look expensive," <<he>> adds, giving you a wink.
				<br><br>
			<<elseif $worn.upper.type.includes("maid") or $worn.lower.type.includes("maid") or $worn.head.type.includes("maid")>>
				<<He>> smiles and raises an eyebrow at your maid dress. "You know, I do like the look of you in that," <<he>> says. "You aren't actually <<= $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("lounge") ? `my` : `a`>> maid, but you do look cute <<= $player.gender_appearance is "m" ? `in a dress, my boy` : `dressed as one`>>." <<He>> winks at you.
				<br><br>
			<<elseif _fullyNaked>>
				<<He>> smiles and looks you up and down, lingering on your bare <<chestsimple>> and exposed <<genitals>>. "Are you trying to tempt me, <<pcpetname "Avery">>? If so," <<He>> leans in to whisper in your ear. "It's working." <<npcincr Avery lust 2>><<glust>>
				<br><br>
			<<elseif $worn.upper.reveal gte 700 or $worn.lower.reveal gte 700>>
				<<He>> smiles and looks you up and down, lingering on your
				<<if $worn.upper.reveal gte 700>>
					<<print $worn.upper.name>>.
				<<else>>
					<<print $worn.lower.name>>.
				<</if>>
				"Are you trying to entice me, <<pcpetname "Avery">>? If so," <<he>> leans in to whisper in your ear. "It's working." <<npcincr Avery lust 1>><<glust>>
				<br><br>
			<<else>>
				<<He>> looks you up and down, and says, "You look <<cute>> today, <<pcpetname "Avery">>." <<He>> smiles and puts a hand on the small of your back.
				<br><br>
			<</if>>
		<</if>>

	<<elseif _chat.misc is 3>> /* The room you're in */
		<<if $avery_mansion.schedule is "drink">>
			<<He>> tells you about <<his>> collection of expensive liquors. It sounds like something <<he>> boasts about a lot.<<if $avery_fate is "saved">> You notice <<he>> doesn't mention the bottle of cheap bourbon you'd seen <<him>> drinking from when <<he>> came back from the hospital.<</if>>
			<br><br>
			<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("lounge") and $avery_mansion.lounge gte 1>>
				At the end of the conversation, <<he>> points out that the lounge needs tidying.
				<br><br>
			<</if>>
		<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "pool">>
			<<if $avery_pool is "coffee">>
				<<He>> tells you from where <<his>> coffee was sourced, the subtle notes in its flavour, and how well regarded the beans themselves are amongst <<his>> set.
				<br><br>
				The world of coffee is more complicated than you thought.
				<br><br>
			<<else>>
				<<He>> tells you about <<his>> exercise regimen, including swimming. "It's important to exercise to maintain one's figure." <<He>> looks you up and down, then smiles and places a hand on your thigh. "Though you look <<cute>> no matter what, <<pcpetname "Avery">><<if $averyragerevealed is 1>>, it's important that you don't get too complacent<</if>>."
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

			<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("pool") and $avery_mansion.pool gte 1>>
				At the end of the conversation, <<he>> points out that the pool needs cleaning.
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

		<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "garden">>
			<<rng 1 2>>
			After a while, <<he>> gets back to pruning <<his>> garden while you watch <<him>> work.
			<<if $rng is 1 and !$averySeen.includes("flower")>>
				The subject of flowers comes up. "I prefer white roses myself," <<he>> says as <<he>> examines the bush in front of <<him>>.
				<<if C.npc.Avery.love gte 60 and C.npc.Avery.rage lt 20 and !$averySeen.includes("flower")>>
					<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("flower")>>
					"And what about you, <<pcpetname "Avery">>?" You tell <<him>> your favourite flower, and <<he>> hums in acknowledgement. "I see. I'll keep that in mind."
				<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<<else>>
				You note that <<he>> is very meticulous in <<his>> work.
				<br><br>
				<<if currentSkillValue('tending') lt 600>>
					<span class="gold">You learn a thing or two about tending gardens.</span> <<gtending>><<tending 6>>
				<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

			<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("garden") and $avery_mansion.garden gte 1>>
				At the end of the conversation, <<he>> points out that the garden needs weeding.
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

		<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "lounge">>
			<<if C.npc.Avery.rage lt 20>> /* Watching football */
				<<rng 1 2>>
				After a while, <<his>> attention returns to the football game.
				<<if $rng is 1>>
					<<He>> seems to be enjoying it, up until the team <<he>> was rooting for misses the winning goal.
					<<He>> goes on a rant about what the player in question ought to have done different. It's all that <<he>> talks about for the rest of the conversation.
				<<else>>
					<<He>> explains the game to you as it progresses. <<= $athletics gte 600 ? `You already understand the rules of the sport, but you let <<him>> go on.` : `You struggle to follow along.`>>
				<</if>>
			<<else>> /* Watching the news */
				<<He>> keeps an eye on the screen as you talk.

				An advertisement for a new model of sports car starts playing. <<He>> <<= either(`is immediately captivated` : `nitpicks at the features it boasts`)>>. When the advertisement is over, <<he>> starts talking about cars in general, then about <<his>> own cars. It's all that <<he>> talks about for the rest of the conversation.
			<</if>>
			<<tiredness 1>><<gtiredness>>
			<br><br>
			<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("lounge") and $avery_mansion.lounge gte 1>>
				At the end of the conversation, <<he>> points out that the lounge needs tidying.
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

		<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "study">>
			<<if $englishtrait gte random(1, 4)>>
				You recognise the book <<hes>> reading. It's <<= either(`a nonfiction`,`a fantasy`,`an erotic`)>> novel. <<= either(`You haven't`,`You've`)>> read it before, and ask for <<his>> thoughts on it.
			<<else>>
				You don't recognise the book <<he>> reading. You ask <<him>> about it.
			<</if>>
			Avery seems pleased to be asked for <<his>> opinion. <<= either(
			`"This is one of my favourite books," <<he>> says. "I read it until it got worn out. This is my second copy."`,
			`"It's a new book from my favourite author," <<he>> says. "I've heard good reviews about it, so I'm trying it out. I'm enjoying it so far."`,
			`"It's something a colleague recommended to me. It's<<if $averyragerevealed is 1>> awful, honestly," <<he>> says. "But I promised that I'd give it a read."<<else>> fine," <<he>> says, with a somewhat strained smile.<</if>>`,
			`"It's something a colleague recommended to me. It's an entertaining read so far," <<he>> says.`
			)>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "bath">>
			<<He>> <<= either(`has you rub <<his>> shoulders`,`has you wash <<his>> back`,`talks in depth about <<his>> beauty regimen`)>> as <<he>> bathes.
			<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("bathroom") and $avery_mansion.bathroom gte 1>>
				At the end of the conversation, <<he>> points out that the bathroom needs cleaning.
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif $avery_mansion.schedule is "breakfast">>
			<<if C.npc.Avery.dom gte 40 and $housekeeping gte 700>>
				<<He>> glances at you, then back to <<his>> meal. "If only I had the time for you to make breakfast<<if $averyragerevealed gte 1>> for me<</if>>, too," <<he>> says. "I'm sure it would be delicious."
			<<else>>
				<<He>> sighs. "I wish I had the time for a more fulfilling breakfast in the morning," <<he>> says. "Unfortunately, I'm far too busy."
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
			<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("dining") and $avery_mansion.dining gte 1>>
				At the end of the conversation, <<he>> points out that the dining room needs cleaning.
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<</if>>
	<<elseif _chat.misc is 4>>
		"I am quite fond of cats," <<he>> says at one point. "There's something about them that speaks to me."
		<br><br>
		You ask why <<he>> doesn't have a cat <<himself>>.
		<<if $wolfgirl gte 2 or $cat gte 2>>
			<<He>> stares at you for a moment before <<he>> smiles. Reaching over to you, <<he>> <<= C.npc.Avery.rage gte 40 ? `pulls on one of your pointed ears, then scratches behind it` : `scratches behind your pointed ears`>>. You can't help but purr. <<arousal 50>><<garousal>>
			<br><br>
			"Why should I? It seems I have <<= $cat gte 2 ? `one` : `a puppy`>> already," <<he>> teases.
			<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
				"Speaking of which, be careful not to get fur all over the place." <<He>> pulls <<his>> hand away, shaking it to get a few strands of fur off.<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("mansion")>> "You don't want to make more of a mess for you to clean, do you?"<</if>>
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<else>>
			"I don't have time for pets. And they're so messy," <<he>> explains with a huff.
			<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20 and ($wolfgirl gte 2 or $cat gte 2 or $cow gte 2 or $harpy gte 6)>>
				"Speaking of which, be careful not to get <<= $harpy gte 2 ? `feathers` : `fur`>> all over the place." <<He>> reaches over and plucks <<= $harpy gte 2 ? `a loose feather` : `a few strands of fur`>> off your shoulder.<<if $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("lounge")>> "You don't want to make more of a mess for you to clean, do you?"<</if>>
			<<elseif $avery_mansion.jobs.includes("lounge")>>
				"You wouldn't want more of a mess to clean, do you?"
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<</if>>
	<<elseif _chat.misc is 5>>
		<<if $avery_valentines and $avery_valentines.end isnot "none" and !$avery_valentines.end_talk>>
			<<set $avery_valentines.end_talk to true>>
			The date you had on Valentine's Day eventually comes up.
			<<if $avery_valentines.end is "good">>
				<<He>> smiles at you, and says, "I still remember that night fondly.<<if $averyromance>>" <<He>> chuckles. "As do you, I'm sure.<</if>>"
			<<else>> /* Bad or neutral */
				<<He>> sighs<<if $averyragereveled is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 40>> curtly<</if>>. "If only it could have ended on a far sweeter note," <<he>> remarks<<if $avery_valentines.end is "bad">> with a flash of irritation on <<his>> face<</if>>.
			<</if>>
		<<else>>
			You talk about the weather. Despite the length of the conversation, neither of you say much at all.
		<</if>>
		<br><br>
	<<else>> /* Weather */
		<<rng 1 2>>
		<<if $rng is 1 and Time.season is "winter">>
			"I do enjoy winter," <<he>> says, looking <<= $outside is 1 ? `up at the sky` : `out the window`>>
			<<if !Weather.precipitation is "none">>
				with a smile. "And it's a perfect day out today, don't you think? It's not often you have a sunny day around this time of year."
			<<else>>
				with a content smile. "Nothing as energising as a cold winter's day, don't you think?"
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif $avery_fate and Weather.bloodMoon>>
			Avery seems distracted tonight. More than once as you talk, you notice <<him>> <<= $outside is 1 ? `glance up` : `staring out the window`>> at the blood moon with
			<<if $avery_fate is "ascended">>
				a <<= either(`solemn`,`contemplative`,`difficult to read`)>>
			<<else>>
				<<= either(`an uneasy`,`an exhausted`,`a difficult to read`)>>
			<</if>>
			expression.
			<br><br>
		<<elseif !Weather.isOvercast and Time.dayState is "day">>
			<<if $avery_mansion.schedule is "pool">>
				"Perfect weather for a
				<<if $avery_pool is "coffee">>
					swim, don't you think?"
					<<avery_injury_check>>
					<<if _avery_injured>>
						<<He>> then <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? `glowers` : `frowns`>> at <<his>> cast, and sighs. "If only I could take advantage," <<he>> mutters.
					<</if>>
				<<elseif $avery_pool is "sunbathe">>
					sunbath," <<he>> says, stretching with a contented sigh.
				<<else>>
					swim, don't you think?" <<he>> says, swishing <<his>> legs in the water.<<if C.npc.Avery.love gte 50>> "You should join me sometime."<</if>>
				<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<<else>>
				"It's a nice day out today," <<he>> says. "Wouldn't you agree, <<= C.npc.Avery.love gte 60 ? `my little sunshine` : C.npc.Avery.love gte 30 ? `sunshine` : `<<pcpetname "Avery">>`>>?"
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

		<<elseif Weather.isOvercast>>
			<<if $outside is 1 and Weather.precipitation isnot "none">>
				<<if $worn.handheld.type.includes("rainproof")>>
					You're lucky you have your <<print $worn.handheld.name>>. You hold it over yourself and Avery, keeping you both safe from the rain.
				<<elseif $avery_pool is "coffee">>
					The table you sit at has an umbrella attachment, so both of you are safe from the rain.
				<<elseif $bus is "avery_garden">>
					Both of you ignore the falling rain. The branches of a nearby tree keep you somewhat dry.
				<<else>> /* Pool */
					Both of you ignore the rain that falls. Every now and then, one of you is startled by a rain drop landing too close to an eye.
				<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<<elseif $outside is 0 and Weather.precipitation isnot "none">>
				<<if $avery_mansion.schedule is "study">> /* Aesthetic™ */
					As you talk, Avery puts on a vinyl of <<= either(`jazz`,`classical music`)>>. The music, the muffled sounds of rain outside, and the closed in atmosphere of the study is relaxing. <<stress -6>><<lstress>><<trauma -3>><<ltrauma>>
				<<else>>
					"Raining, hm?" Avery frowns. "<<= Time.weekDay isnot 7 and Time.hour lte 6 ? `I should bring an umbrella with me to work.` : `At least we're inside.`>>"
				<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<<else>>
				"Cloudy out today, isn't it?" Avery frowns.
				<<if Time.weekDay isnot 7 and Time.hour lte 6>>
					"I wonder if it's going to rain. Perhaps I should bring an umbrella with me to work, just in case."
				<<elseif $outside is 0>>
					"I wonder if it's going to rain. If it does, at least we're inside."
				<<else>>
					"I wonder if it's going to rain."
				<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

		<<else>>
			You talk about the weather. Despite the length of the conversation, neither of you say much at all.
			<br><br>
		<</if>>
	<</if>>

	<<endevent>>
	<<avery_mansion_end_links>>
<</if>>


:: Mansion Talk Chat Locket
<<effects>>

<<if $phase is 2>> /* Show */
	You show Avery what's inside your love locket. Inside is a picture of <<= $carried.neck.photo is "Avery" ? `<<him>>` : `<<print $carried.neck.photo>>`>>.
	<br><br>
	<<if $carried.neck.photo is "Avery">>
		<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
			<<He>> raises an eyebrow at it and hums. "You'll forgive my surprise. Given how rebellious you can be, I was beginning to wonder." Then <<he>> <<laughs>>. "But I suppose it's only to be expected."
		<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
			"My, my." <<He>> smirks. "How flattering, <<pcpetname "Avery">>." <<He>> seems satisfied.
		<<else>>
			<<He>> lets out a small laugh. "Why, how <<= either(`sweet`,`lovely`,`charming`)>>, <<pcpetname "Avery">>." <<He>> puts a hand on the small of your back.<<if $averyragerevealed is 1>> <<He>> seems satisfied.<</if>>
		<</if>><<npcincr Avery rage -1>><<npcincr Avery love 1>><<larage>><<glove>>
		<br><br>
		<<endevent>>
		<<avery_mansion_end_links>>

	<<else>>
		Upon seeing it, <<he>>
		<<if $carried.neck.photo is "Robin">>
			<<if $robinaverybeat is 1>>
				glowers. "Ah. That brat. You remember what <<nnpc_he "Robin">> did to me, don't you? Why are you keeping a photo of <<nnpc_him "Robin">> on you?" <<npcincr Avery rage 3>><<ggarage>>
			<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
				scowls. "I told you not to associate with <<nnpc_his "Robin">> sort, didn't I?" <<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
			<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
				frowns. "Ah. That <<nnpc_gendery "Robin">>. You know, one might think you would keep a picture of your <<nnpc_girlfriend "Avery">> in a love locket, rather than a schoolmate," <<he>> says with a too careful nonchalance. <<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
			<<else>>
				raises an eyebrow. "Ah. Isn't this your friend? The one you walk to school with from time to time?"<<if $averyragerevealed is 1>> <<He>> frowns.<</if>> <<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif $carried.neck.photo is "Whitney">>
			<<if $averySeen.includes("whitney_crash")>>
				glowers. "The <<nnpc_gendery "Whitney">> that stole my car? You remember what <<nnpc_he "Whitney">> did to it, don't you? Why are you keeping a photo of <<nnpc_him "Whitney">> on you?" <<npcincr Avery rage 5>><<ggarage>>
			<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
				scowls. "What is the meaning of this, <<girl>>?" <<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
			<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
				frowns. "One might think you would keep a picture of your <<nnpc_girlfriend "Avery">> in a locket, rather than a schoolmate," <<he>> says with a too careful nonchalance. <<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
			<<else>>
				raises an eyebrow. "Ah. And who is this, exactly? <<nnpc_He "Whitney">> seems," <<he>> says, then pauses.<<if $averyragerevealed is 1>> <<His>> lip curls.<</if>> It appears <<hes>> unable to think of anything polite to say. <<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
			<</if>>
			<br><br>
		<<elseif $carried.neck.photo is "Sydney">>
			<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
				scowls. "What is the meaning of this, <<girl>>?"
			<<elseif $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 20>>
				frowns. "One might think you would keep a picture of your <<nnpc_girlfriend "Avery">> in a locket, rather than a schoolmate," <<he>> says with a too careful nonchalance.
			<<else>>
				raises an eyebrow. "Ah. And who is this, exactly?
				<<if $averySeen.includes("temple_prospective")>>
					Someone from the temple?"
