<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"Two of your staff assaulted me upstairs," you say. "You need to do a better job making sure your hires are trustworthy."
<<else>>
	"I was assaulted by two of your staff," you say. "I recognised their voices."
<</if>>
<br><br>

Avery waits for you to finish speaking, then waits a moment longer. "Two left in a hurry." <<His>> voice is cold. <<He>> produces <<his>> phone, taps something into it, then puts it away.
