:: Mansion Mickey Interrupt
<<effects>><<summon_brown_fox 1>><<person1>>

"Psst."
<br><br>
You look in the direction of the voice. Mickey hides in the shade of a tree, and waves you over.
<br><br>

"I'm here about that job Landry gave you," they say. "The wishing stones. I'm on it too. I've been attacking Avery from every angle, but I'm not finding much. Wherever the stones are, they're off-grid."
<br><br>

Mickey pauses, and looks anywhere but your eyes, as if ashamed. "I haven't found the stones, but I've found other things. Avery has," they pause again. "Intense tastes." They pause yet again, then fix you with their gaze, determined to say their piece. "<span class="pink">If Avery felt dominant,</span> <<nnpc_he Avery>> might slip up. Reveal the stones' location. Nothing to fear from <<nnpc_his Avery>> 'pet', right? I know I know, it's messed up, but it's an option."
<br><br>

Mickey shakes their hands, as if removing something filthy. "There must be another way, but it's beyond me. I'm sorry. Avery has a plan for them. The stones. <span class="pink">If <<nnpc_he Avery>> finishes <<nnpc_his Avery>> skyscraper,</span> then it could be too late."
<br><br>

<<if isGwylanAbsent()>>
	"Your approach is up to you. You're the field agent. The one in the thick of it. I'll keep doing what I can." Mickey glances over their shoulder. "Good luck." They turn and leave, weaving between the trees.
	<br><br>

	<<set $avery_mansion.mickey to 1>>

	<<link [[Next|Danube Street]]>><<endevent>><<set $eventskip to 1>><</link>>
