:: Mansion Brown Fox Wounded
<<effects>><<summon_brown_fox 1>><<person1>>

You feel the hairs on the back of your neck stand up as you walk down Danube Boulevard. A rustle from a nearby tree grabs your attention.
<br><br>

A figure drops out of it gracefully, but stumbles after a moment. It's <<say_brown_fox>>. <<He>> waves you over.
<br><br>

"<<if !$avery_mansion.fox.dungeon>>Listen. I've got a lead on the bones, but it cost me. <</if>>I'm compromised." <span class="red">There's some fresh bandages wrapped around <<his>> upper right leg. The centre is still dark with blood.</span>
From this close up, you also notice that what little of <<his>> face you can see is <span class="lewd">deeply flushed</span>.
<<if Weather.temperature <= 5>>
	<<He>> breathes heavily, and you can see each breath in the cold air.
<<else>>
	<<He>> breathes heavily.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> notices you staring. "It's just a graze. It's not my first, and it won't be my last. The important thing is, the Elks only suspect a petty thief at work, and they've got no trail on me. Except that one." <<He>> points to the end of a faint blood trail.
<<He>> lets out a long breath, trying to compose <<himself>>. "The chase was exciting. Pardon my unprofessional look.
<<if $avery_mansion.fox.remy_warn>>
	It's thanks to you that I was able to give the High Elk the slip with only this."
<<else>>
	I gave the High Elk some wounds of <<nnpc_his "Remy">> own."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> takes your arm and pulls you into a crouch behind the tree.
<<if !$fake_artefact>>
	"You're an accomplice now, whether you like it or not, so listen well. We're searching for a precious artefact. Landry at the pub can tell you more." <<He>> shivers.
<</if>>
<<if $avery_mansion.fox.dungeon>>
	"I'm certain that the dungeon you've told me about will have the vault. It will have a code, for certain. The problem will be getting in and finding it." <<He>> pauses. "I can think of one way. <span class="pink">If you make <<nnpc_him "Avery">> mad enough.</span>"
<<else>>
	"Somewhere in the mansion, there's going to be a vault, and that vault will have a code. I don't know where, but if I were to hazard a guess, it would be somewhere disgusting. A place Avery wouldn't want anyone seeing."
	<<He>> pauses. "Except <<nnpc_his "Avery">> favourite toy. <<if $avery_mansion.mickey>>Mickey already told you that, though.<</if>> There might be another way, if you can't stand being Avery's pet. <<nnpc_Hes "Avery">> deeply insecure." <<He>> swallows heavily.
	"<span class="pink">If you make <<nnpc_him "Avery">> mad enough, <<nnpc_he "Avery">> might just throw <<nnpc_his "Avery">> weight around and slip up.</span>"
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> sits back, still breathing heavily. "It'll be dangerous if you decide to go that route. It'll probably hurt. Bad." <<He>> clutches <<his>> wounded leg and winces for a moment. "Worse than this, maybe." <<He>> tries to stand up.
"Unfortunately, I won't be able to help much more like this. I'm sorry."
<br><br>

<<set $avery_mansion.fox.task to false>>
<<set $avery_mansion.fox.task_complete to false>>
<<set $avery_mansion.fox.task_detail to false>>

