<<effects>>

<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
	"It's wonderful," you say. "Thank you. Would you like to come in?"
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"I'm glad people miss me," you say. "Come inside."
<<else>>
	"Thank you," you say. "Would you like to come in?"
<</if>>
<br><br>

Robin takes another glance at the mansion, then steps back in trepidation. "I can't. It would feel wrong." <<He>> flashes a smile. "I'll be happy to see you at the orphanage. It's good you're still nearby, and not further way."
<br><br>

<<He>> puts <<his>> arms through the bars to hug you as best <<he>> can, then <<he>> walks down the boulevard.
<br><br>

You look again at the folder Robin gave you. What do you do with it?
