:: Mansion Fox Heist
<<set $outside to 0>><<effects>><<summon_brown_fox 1>><<person1>>
<<set $avery_mansion.heist_suspicion to 0>>
<<if $phase is 1>>
	You play the six familiar notes on the piano, and wait.
<<else>>
	<<set $avery_mansion.heist_suspicion++>>
	You whistle the six familiar notes, and wait.
<</if>>
<br><br>

You continue waiting for a while. You wonder if <<say_brown_fox>> is even close enough to have heard you.
<br><br>

You're about to stand up, when you hear a rustle from outside the mansion grounds. <span class="green">A brown fox mask peeks up from over the wall, and a pair of green eyes lock onto you.</span>
<br><br>

<<He>> hoists <<himself>> over and lands gracefully,
<<if $phase is 1>>
	before skulking into the lounge with you. "Creative. Playing it on the piano is much less out of place.
<<else>>
	before skulking over to you. "I was camping out nearby.
<</if>>
Let's get moving, before Avery gets wise."
<br><br>

<<if $exposedRaw gte 2>>
	<<He>> stands in front of you for another brief moment, notably not looking down at your <<lewdness>>. "Must be chilly in here."
	<br><br>
<</if>>

<<link [[Next|Mansion Fox Heist 2]]>><<pass 5>><</link>>
<br>

:: Mansion Fox Heist 2
<<effects>>
You sneak up towards Avery's study. <<say_brown_fox "cap">> whispers to you. "It feels much different in here without guests around. Larger." <<He>> frowns. "No one person needs all of this."
<br><br>

<<if currentSkillValue("skulduggery") gte 600>>
	<span class="green">You keep up with <<his>> stealthy stride.</span>
<<else>>
	<<set $avery_mansion.heist_suspicion++>>
	<span class="red">It's hard for you to keep up with <<his>> stealthy stride.</span>
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> leans against the wall around a corner, and you join <<him>>. "Would you be willing to leave this all behind? Is Avery worth it?"
<br><br>

<<link [[Yes|Mansion Fox Heist 3]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[No|Mansion Fox Heist 3]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
<br>

:: Mansion Fox Heist 3
<<effects>>
<<if $phase is 1>>
	You nod.
	<br><br>

	"Wait, yes you'd be willing to leave it all behind? Or yes that Avery is worth it?"
<<else>>
	You shake your head.
	<br><br>

	"Wait, no you wouldn't be willing to leave it all behind? Or no that Avery isn't worth it?"
<</if>>
<<He>> scratches <<his>> head. "Sorry, let me try that again.
<<if $averyragerevealed>>
	<span class="red">Are those bruises worth it?</span> Are they worth this life of luxury? I would ask if a safe home is worth it, but it's plain to see this is neither safe, nor a home."
<<else>>
	Is doing Avery's every whim worth it? Is this plastic house a life you find fulfilling?"
<</if>>
<<He>> pauses. "I'm not trying to guide your answer. I'm just curious."
<br><br>

<<link [[Say you like it here|Mansion Fox Heist 4]]>><<pass 5>><<set $phase to 0>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say it's better than the orphanage|Mansion Fox Heist 4]]>><<pass 5>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<if $soldCount gte 2>>
	<<link [[Say it's better than being sold as a sex slave|Mansion Fox Heist 4]]>><<pass 5>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>
<<link [[Say it's Hell|Mansion Fox Heist 4]]>><<pass 5>><<set $phase to 3>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you're doing this to get back at Avery|Mansion Fox Heist 4]]>><<pass 5>><<set $phase to 4>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say nothing|Mansion Fox Heist 4]]>><<pass 5>><<set $phase to 5>><</link>>
<br>

:: Mansion Fox Heist 4
<<effects>>

<<if $phase is 0>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"I'm quite comfortable here. It's a pleasure to serve my betters," you say in a dignified tone.
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"I don't want for much here. The food is good, there's a pool, everything I could ever want," you say.
	<<else>>
		"It's comfortable here. I don't mind serving to pay for it," you say.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<if $speech_attitude isnot "meek" and $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"I don't like the way your attitude changed when you said that. You're speaking as if Avery were listening."
	<</if>>
	<<He>> frowns. "I hope this changes Avery for the better. Truly. But, sometimes..."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> slowly reaches a hand towards your face, and caresses your cheek. There's a deep, tired sadness behind what little you can see of <<his>> eyes for a moment.
	<br><br>

	"Sometimes, the only way to save a flower is to cut it away from the rotten roots that bind it, and replant it for a fresh start." <<He>> pulls away. "That isn't my choice to make, though."
<<elseif $phase is 1>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"Avery treats me well, much better than Bailey."
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"If I'm going to suffer, I'd rather suffer in comfort. It's better than Bailey."
	<<else>>
		"Avery treats me better than Bailey does," you say.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> winces.
	<<if $speech_attitude isnot "meek" and $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"I don't like the way your attitude changed when you said that. You're speaking as if <<nnpc_he "Avery">> were listening."
	<</if>>
	There's a long silence.
	<br><br>

	"Is Bailey..." <<He>> stops <<himself>>, and shakes <<his>> head. "Never mind."
<<elseif $phase is 2>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"At least I'm not being sold to others anymore, like Bailey was doing," you say.
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"At least I'm not Bailey's property anymore, to be sold off to the highest bidder," you say.
	<<else>>
		"At least I'm not being sold into sex slavery anymore," you say,
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<if $speech_attitude isnot "meek" and $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"I don't like the way your attitude changed when you said that. You're speaking as if Avery were listening."
	<</if>>
	<<He>> frowns. "But... isn't that exactly what happened? Did Bailey not sell you to Avery? Like a piece of merchandise?"
	<br><br>

	You open your mouth to respond, but you can't formulate any argument to the contrary. <span class="red"><<Hes>> right.</span> <<trauma 3>><<gtrauma>>
	<br><br>

	"I'm sorry, but a cage remains a cage, no matter how gilded. The bird always yearns for freedom."
<<elseif $phase is 3>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
		"This is awful," you say. "I hate it here."
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"This place is a living hell. I want out."
	<<else>>
		"If hell is real, I imagine it's something like this."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> puts a hand on your shoulder. "It'll be over soon. I promise. I'm not just doing this to end Avery's occult ambitions. I'm doing it for you, too." <<He>> smiles. "Let's keep moving, <<pcpetname "Gwylan" "simple">>, the keys to freedom await."
<<elseif $phase is 4>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
		"I'm doing this to teach Avery a lesson," you say. "Even if we're saving <<nnpc_him "Avery">>, it will humble <<nnpc_him "Avery">>." You pause. "I hope."
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"I'm doing this out of spite. Avery deserves to have <<nnpc_his "Avery">> ambitions ruined, whether it's for <<nnpc_his "Avery">> own good or not."
	<<else>>
		"We might be doing this to save Avery from <<nnpc_himself "Avery">>, but I'm hoping it will teach <<nnpc_him "Avery">> a lesson too."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> smiles. "That's the spirit. Hold onto that. We're doing a good thing. For you, for Avery, for everyone."
<<else>>
	You look down silently. <<He>> frowns, but doesn't press the question.
<</if>>
<br><br>

You reach the third floor.
<<if $avery_mansion.study_unlocked>>
	The door to the study is already unlocked.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[Next|Mansion Fox Heist Unlock]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	<<set $lock to 1000>>
	The door to the study is locked tight.
	<br><br>

	<<if currentSkillValue('skulduggery') gte $lock>>
		<<if $leftarm is "bound" and $rightarm is "bound">>
			You think you'd be able to pick the lock, <span class="blue">if your arms weren't bound.</span>
		<<else>>
			<<wearProp "lockpick">>
			<span class="green">The lock looks easy to pick.</span>
			<br><br>
			<<lockicon "pick">><<link [[Break in (0:05)|Mansion Fox Heist Unlock]]>><<set $phase to 1>><<pass 5>><</link>>
		<</if>>
	<<else>>
		<span class="red">The lock looks beyond your ability to pick.</span><<skulduggeryrequired>>
	<</if>>
	<br>
	<<link [[Let <<say_brown_fox>> handle it|Mansion Fox Heist Unlock]]>><<set $phase to 2>><<pass 10>><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>

:: Mansion Fox Heist Unlock
<<effects>>
<<if $phase is 1>>
	You deftly pick the lock to the study. <<say_brown_fox "cap">> giggles. "Are you sure you needed my help?"
<<else>>
	<<set $avery_mansion.heist_suspicion += 1>>
	<<say_brown_fox "cap">> kneels, and examines the lock. "This is advanced. I wouldn't be able to pick it." <<He>> produces a strange phial from under <<his>> cloak, along with a lighter. The phial has a small metal rod driven through the bottom, and is filled with a thick wax.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> pops open the phial, and holds the open end over the lock. <<He>> then ignites the lighter and holds it to the glass. Over the course of a minute, the wax expands, pushing itself into the lock. Once it's in place, <<he>> removes the lighter.
	<br><br>

	"The lock will be sticky for a while. Avery might notice." <<He>> jiggles the phial, and turns the metal rod. <span class="green">You hear a click.</span> <<He>> opens the door, and waits for the strange wax to shrink again. It crackles as it disengages from the lock.
<</if>>
You enter.
<br><br>

<<if $avery_mansion.study_secret is 2>>
	You lead <<say_brown_fox>> over to the red leather-bound book. <<He>> frowns when <<he>> sees what Avery did to the pages within.
	<br><br>

	You take the remote, and press the button. You hear a mechanical whirring, and the desk splits in two, revealing the spiral staircase down to the dungeon.
<<elseif $avery_mansion.study_secret is 1>>
	<<set $avery_mansion.study_secret to 2>>
	You feel along the bookshelf, right where Avery stood when <<nnpc_he Avery>> opened the way to the dungeon. There are tiny scratches in the wood. You remember hearing <<nnpc_his Avery>> watch scrape against it.
	<br><br>

	You check the book beneath the scratches, bound in red leather.
	<br>
	<i>"The Cult of Auriga: An Esoteric History"</i>
	<br>
	You open it. A rectangle has been gouged into the pages, removing the paper, and creating a space large enough to conceal a remote. There's a single button. You press it.
	<br><br>

	You hear a mechanical whirring, and the desk splits in two, revealing the spiral staircase down to the dungeon.
	<br><br>

	<<say_brown_fox "cap">> remains staring at the book, frowning at what Avery did to the pages within.
<<else>>
	<<set $avery_mansion.study_secret to 2>><<set $avery_mansion.heist_suspicion += 2>>
	"So, you know it's somewhere in here." <<He>> begins to look around, inspecting everything.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> runs <<his>> hands along the desk. <<He>> moves back, and sits on top of it. <<He>> sways left to right, lightly shaking it. "Aha!"
	<<He>> hops off, and crawls underneath. "There are some... stains under here. But there's something else, too. The desk is segmented, as if..." <<He>> knocks on the ground. "It's here. We just need to figure out how to open it."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> inspects the bookshelves, running <<his>> hands along them next. <<He>> stops. "Here. Scratch marks." <<He>> takes a book from underneath them, bound in red leather.
	<br>
	<i>"The Cult of Auriga: An Esoteric History"</i>
	<br>
	<<He>> opens it. A rectangle has been gouged into the pages, removing the paper, and creating a space large enough to conceal a remote. There's a single button. <<He>> stares at the violated pages, frowning.
	<br><br>

	You step closer and press the button yourself. You hear a mechanical whirring, and the desk splits in two, revealing the spiral staircase down to the dungeon.
	<br><br>

	<<say_brown_fox "cap">> remains staring at the book.
<</if>>
<br><br>

You snap your fingers in front of <<him>>, which gets <<his>> attention. "Sorry."
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|Mansion Fox Heist Dungeon]]>><<pass 5>><</link>>
<br>

:: Mansion Fox Heist Dungeon
<<effects>>

You walk down the spiral staircase, down the ominous hallway, and into Avery's dungeon. <<say_brown_fox "cap">> is right behind you, holding one of your shoulders.
<br><br>

You're bathed in eerie red light. <<He>> stops, looking around at the tools.
<br><br>

You try to walk forwards, but <<hes>> still holding your shoulder.
<br><br>

<<link [[Ask if <<hes>> alright|Mansion Fox Heist Dungeon 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Pull <<his>> hand away|Mansion Fox Heist Dungeon 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
<br>

:: Mansion Fox Heist Dungeon 2
<<effects>>
<<if $phase is 1>>
	You gently put your hand on <<hers>>.
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
		"Are you okay? You're all stiff."
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"Hey, are you broken?"
	<<else>>
		"Are you alright? You're holding on pretty tightly."
	<</if>>
<<else>>
	You pull <<his>> hand off of you.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> shakes <<his>> head. "Sorry, again. Just a bad memory." <<His>> gaze is fixed on the whips. <<He>> forces <<himself>> to look elsewhere, and sees the vault beyond.
<br><br>

The two of you approach the thick, silvery metal door of the vault. Beside it is a keypad.
<br><br>

<<say_brown_fox "cap">> kneels down and opens a satchel under <<his>> cloak. <<He>> produces a small spray bottle and uses it on the keypad. The smell of the mist stings your nostrils.
<br><br>

<<He>> unrolls a plastic-looking film, holds it against the keypad, and sprays the opposite side with the same bottle. <span class="gold">Smudges appear over four of the keys.</span>
<br><br>

"Nine, eight, seven, and five. Now we just need the order." <<He>> begins trying every combination of those four digits.
<br><br>

<<link [[Wait quietly|Mansion Fox Heist Vault]]>><<pass 10>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<if $brownFoxRevealed>>
	<<if !$brownFoxMaskTalk>>
		<<link [[Ask about <<his>> mask|Mansion Fox Heist Vault]]>><<pass 10>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>
<<else>>
	<<link [[Ask if you can know who <<he>> really is now|Mansion Fox Heist Vault]]>><<pass 10>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>
<<link [[Ask what personal stake <<he>> has in all this|Mansion Fox Heist Vault]]>><<pass 10>><<set $phase to 3>><</link>>
<br>

:: Mansion Fox Heist Vault
<<avery_mansion>>
<<effects>>
<<if $phase is 1>>
	You watch <<say_brown_fox>> work, keeping a professional silence between you.
<<elseif $phase is 2>>
	<<if $brownFoxRevealed>>
		<<set $brownFoxMaskTalk to true>>
		<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
			"Why are you hiding your face like that?
		<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
			"So, what's with all the cloak and dagger?
		<<else>>
			"Why are you hiding your identity like this?
		<</if>>
		Do they really not know who you are by now?"
		<br><br>

		<<He>> giggles. "No. I'm quite easy to forget. It's easier if they suspect some masked vigilante. If they started suspecting otherwise..." <<he>> pauses. "They might start making some connections. Dangerous ones."
		<br><br>

		"So why a fox mask?" you ask.
		<br><br>

		<<He>> stops touching the keypad, and looks down. "It's symbolic. I want them to see the face of their victims biting back." <<He>> removes the mask, and rubs the cheek.
		"When I wear this, I'm not Gwylan. I'm every single victim of the elks and hounds. I'm their vengeance." <<His>> hands clench slightly. "No one else will give it to them. The Cloister will just make them suffer more, use them as... vessels.
		Us foxes only have each other."
		<br><br>

		<<He>> puts the mask back on. "That's what the brown fox symbolises. The Children of Auriga have a lot to pay for, and all Avery's fake money couldn't pay for a single one."
		<<He>> looks at you over <<his>> shoulder with a sad smile. "I'm glad you're here. We're stronger together."
	<<else>>
		<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
			"Do you trust me enough to tell me who you are?
		<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
			"So, who are you really?
		<<else>>
			"We've been working together for a while. Will you tell me who you really are?
		<</if>>
		<<if $wrenSeen?.includes("cards") or $temple_confessor_intro>>
			I haven't met many others who are so willing to cross these people."
		<<else>>
			I haven't met anyone else so willing to cross these people."
		<</if>>
		<br><br>

		<<He>> continues working. "It's safer for you to not know. Maybe, when this is all over, I'll tell you. Or maybe you'll figure it out for yourself before then."
		<<He>> pauses, and looks back to you. "It's not that I don't trust you. It really is better this way."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
<<else>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
		"So, why are you helping Landry?
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"So, why are you helping me?
	<<else>>
		"So, why are you helping us?
	<</if>>
	This all seems pretty personal. There must be a story behind it."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> pauses. "You aren't wrong. Part of it is personal. Not all of it." <<He>> stands up. "The skyscraper is an affront to nature. Its shadow over the town will spread ill.
	The High Elk and Cannibal Fox seek to turn Avery into their third, the Crimson Hound, through a ritual during the blood moon."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> paces. "That kind of power would ruin <<nnpc_him "Avery">>, and that ruin, that <i>poison</i>, would seep into the world. Everything would become worse. It would be a slow, strangling death."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> stops. "My personal reasons are unimportant." <<He>> kneels back down before the keypad.
<</if>>
<<He>> continues punching in combinations.
<br><br>

"Do you believe someone like Avery could ever redeem <<nnpc_himself "Avery">>?" <<He>> doesn't wait for you to answer. "<<nnpc_Hes "Avery">> a disgusting <<nnpc_gender "Avery">>. <<nnpc_He "Avery">> deserves Hell and high water."
The dull beep of the keypad rings out in between <<his>> words. "We aren't just saving <<nnpc_him "Avery">> from <<nnpc_himself "Avery">>. We're making sure <<nnpc_he "Avery">> doesn't drag us all down with <<nnpc_him "Avery">>."
<<He>> stops after another dull beep. <<He>> stays silent, as if listening for something.
<br><br>

<<if !["away", "work", "pool", "garden"].includes($avery_mansion.schedule) and $avery_mansion.heist_suspicion gte 2>>
	<<if $avery_mansion.schedule is "return">>
		<span class="red">You hear the screech of tires, and the rattle of the front gates. Avery has returned, and will be looking for you.</span>
	<<else>>
		<span class="red">You hear the walls creak, as if in warning. Avery is approaching the study.</span>
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<say_brown_fox "cap">> quickly removes the film from the keypad, looking towards the stairs. "Do you trust me?"
	<br><br>

	<<link [[Yes|Mansion Fox Heist Vault Caught]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
	<br>
	<<link [[No|Mansion Fox Heist Vault Caught]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	When <<he>> doesn't hear anything, <<he>> continues again.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[Next|Mansion Fox Heist Vault 2]]>><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>

:: Mansion Fox Heist Vault Caught
<<effects>>
<<if $phase is 1>>
	<<He>> smiles. "Good. Come here." <span class="red"><<He>> pulls you over to the rack, and starts to strap you into it.</span> "Play along. Get <<nnpc_him "Avery">> to let <<nnpc_his "Avery">> guard down."
<<else>>
	<<He>> smiles. "Unfortunate. I'll leave it to you, then. Get <<nnpc_him "Avery">> to let <<nnpc_his "Avery">> guard down."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> skulks away into a corner, and vanishes in the shadows.
<br><br>

<<endevent "phaseless">><<npc Avery>><<person1>>
