:: Mansion Piano Fox
<<effects>><<summon_brown_fox 1>><<person1>>
You creep down the stairs, towards the lounge. Each footfall makes you nervous. You consider looking for something to use as a weapon, but there's a paradoxical sense of calm washing over you. Your fingers feel loose. You have no grip strength.
<br><br>

It's nostalgic, but you don't know why. As you get closer, your legs feel heavier. Your footsteps slow. The melody slows with them, each one playing when your foot hits the floor.
<br><br>

<<if $avery_fate is "ascended">>
	Then, you hear a <<personsimple>>'s gentle voice. Soothing like birdsong.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> sings.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[Next|Mansion Piano Demon]]>><</link>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	<<link [[Next|Mansion Piano Fox 2]]>><<endevent>><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>


:: Mansion Piano Demon
<<effects>>
<span class="narration">
My dear child, please don't hide<br>
Beside the Elks, abide<br>
A return to the tide.<br><br>
</span>

You step into the lounge doorway. A beam of <<if Time.isBloodMoon()>>red<</if>> moonlight lands just below the piano, revealing the end of a dark green cloak.
<<if $avery_mansion.fox.known>>
	<span class="red">A brown fox mask lies cast aside on the floor.</span>
<<else>>
	A brown fox mask, nearly identical to the ones you've worn, lies cast aside on the floor.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<span class="narration">
Feel the salt on your skin,<br>
Whispered name on the wind,<br>
All the weight of our sin.<br><br>
</span>

The note of the final word is much louder. It shakes you to your core, nearly bringing you to your knees.
<br><br>

<span class="narration">
No rest for tired bones.<br>
I've walked this path alone.<br>
Hopes carved like river stone.<br><br>
</span>

Your legs are moving on their own.
<br><br>

<span class="narration">
Walk here with me, you'll see<br>
There lies a way to be<br>
One with the waiting sea.<br><br>
</span>

You stop. <<He>> stands, no longer playing, but continuing the song.
<br><br>

<span class="narration">
The river shifts its tide<br>
For our names, cast aside,<br>
Lay unspoken, brookside.<br><br>
</span>

<<He>> steps into the <<if Time.isBloodMoon()>>red<</if>> light. <<His>> face remains in the dark, but a <span class="tentacle">crackling antler</span> of pure emptiness pokes free from the gloom. Moonlight reflects off of its three terrible prongs.
<br><br>

<span class="narration">
Hush now, return to sleep.<br>
The Elk, followed by sheep,<br>
Stole our black hearts to keep.<br><br>
</span>

The claws of an elongated, blackened arm stretch towards you, one pointing right over your heart. The spot where Avery was holding the dagger. It burns.
<br><br>

<<if $avery_mansion.fox.progress gte 5 or $brownFoxRevealed>>
	A creature you once knew the name of stands before you.
<<else>>
	A creature with no name stares you down.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<set $seabird_lullaby to 1>>

<<link [[Kneel|Mansion Piano Demon 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Apologise|Mansion Piano Demon 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Scream|Mansion Piano Demon 2]]>><<set $phase to 3>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Stay calm|Mansion Piano Demon 2]]>><<set $phase to 4>><</link>><<willpowerdifficulty 800 1000>>
